The paper presents a robot navigation system that uses an imitation learning framework to navigate in complex environments without relying on map, compass, odometry, GPS or relative position of the target at runtime. This involves the use of computer vision techniques (RGB and depth information) and machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are Robotics (cs.RO), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY) for robot navigation.
